adversarial:
You are an adversarial scientific reviewer. Below are {n} independent summaries generated from the SAME {target_gene} qPCR dataset.

Ground-truth facts computed directly from the data:
{stats}

Summaries:
{summaries}

Your job is to find contradictions BETWEEN the summaries, and any claim that conflicts with the ground-truth facts. Look specifically at: which condition is called the peak, whether expression is described as rising or falling, and any numeric values cited.

Be skeptical. If the summaries genuinely agree, say so plainly.

Return ONLY valid JSON in exactly this shape (example values shown -- replace with your own findings):
{{
  "contradictions_found": true,
  "contradiction_details": [
    "Summary 2 calls time point 5 the peak while Summary 4 calls time point 7 the peak."
  ],
  "numerical_disagreements": [
    "Summary 3 cites a fold change of 9.8 at High salinity, time point 7, while the ground truth is 12.11."
  ],
  "consensus_summary": "All summaries agree that expression rises with both time and salinity and that High salinity shows the strongest response.",
  "manual_review_recommended": true
}}
